Method Detail

textCompact

protected java.lang.String textCompact(java.lang.String str)
Write a CDATA's value to the destination. The value will first be compacted (all leading and trailing whitespace will be removed and all internal whitespace will be be represented with a single ' ' character). If the CDATA contains only whitespace then nothing is output.

The results (if any) will be wrapped in the <![CDATA[ and ]]> delimiters.

Parameters:
str - the CDATA's value.
Returns:
The input String in a compact form

textTrimFullWhite

protected java.lang.String textTrimFullWhite(java.lang.String str)
Write a CDATA's value to the destination. The value will first be inspected. If the CDATA contains only whitespace then nothing is output, otherwise the entire input str will be wrapped in the <![CDATA[ and ]]> delimiters.

Parameters:
str - the CDATA's value.
Returns:
the input str if there's at least one non-whitespace char in it. otherwise returns ""

textTrimBoth

protected java.lang.String textTrimBoth(java.lang.String str)
Write a CDATA's value to the destination. The value will first be trimmed (all leading and trailing whitespace will be removed). If the CDATA contains only whitespace then nothing is output. The results (if any) will be wrapped in the <![CDATA[ and ]]> delimiters.

Parameters:
str - the CDATA's value.
Returns:
the input str value trimmed left and right.

textTrimRight

protected java.lang.String textTrimRight(java.lang.String str)
Write a CDATA's value to the destination. The value will first be right-trimmed (all trailing whitespace will be removed). If the CDATA contains only whitespace then nothing is output. The results (if any) will be wrapped in the <![CDATA[ and ]]> delimiters.

Parameters:
str - the CDATA's value.
Returns:
the input str trimmed on the right.

textTrimLeft

protected java.lang.String textTrimLeft(java.lang.String str)
Write a CDATA's value to the destination. The value will first be left-trimmed (all leading whitespace will be removed). If the CDATA contains only whitespace then nothing is output. The results (if any) will be wrapped in the <![CDATA[ and ]]> delimiters.

Parameters:
str - the CDATA's value.
Returns:
the input str trimmed on the left.
